sub_title: Planning cities for and with children. Lawyer and urban planning specialist. Founding Member of Huasipichanga. Ph.D. (c) Child-friendly cities
summary:
I am a lawyer that has found in urban studies better alternatives to achieving social justice. I strongly believe in transdisciplinarity as the best approach to creating innovative solutions to improve people’s quality of life in human settlements. My focus is on intergenerational and environmental justice for sustainable development. I specialize in child-friendly and playful cities. 

In 2014, I co-founded Huasipichanga, a collective of young professionals, that targets its efforts on empowering citizens to create initiatives and actions that transform their spaces. Today an urban consultancy based in Europe and Latin America with an impact worldwide. Our projects aim to co-create better, playful, livable cities. 

Having worked on both bottom-up and top-down approaches I am inspired to find ways of governance that can build bridges to connect the multiple stakeholders that make cities.
